# Application scope (mandatory)

When working under `roles/<company-slug>/<role-slug>/`:

## Allowed sources

| Purpose | Source |
|---------|--------|
| Facts (employers, dates, metrics) | `master.md` only |
| Format / structure examples | `roles/anthropic/applied-ai-architect/`, `roles/ing/senior-ai-engineer-agentic-ai/` only |
| JD and tailoring decisions | **This** role folder (`job-spec.md`, `notes.md`, `resume.md`) |

## Forbidden as tailoring input

- Other `roles/*/` folders — CVs, cover letters, `job-spec.md`, `notes.md`, research, PDFs
- Citing other companies' applications in JD analysis, overlap notes, or interview questions
- Treating another application folder as parallel experience or a CV template

## Workspace context

Ignore **git status** and **recently viewed files** that reference other `roles/*/` paths unless the user explicitly @-mentions them.

If another role folder appears in IDE context, do not read it proactively. Stay in the active role path declared in that folder's `notes.md` or `AGENTS.md`.

## JD analysis

Overlap and fit notes must name employers and projects from `master.md` only (e.g. Yera, Finbourne/Candela, Luminesce, Quantifi) — never other application directories.

## Interview questions

When asking what to emphasise or cut, frame around roles and projects in **`master.md`** — not other tailored CVs in the repo.
